values: Ok everyone, I know I said I was changing my jounal to "pepprmintblood", but I decided not to, and i've deleted that journal.  To all of you who already added me, I'm sorry for having to ask you to do it again, but my new journal name is: <lj user="bloodpeppermint">.  Please add me!

Last night Evana Sylva called me.  She lived here for a few months four years ago.  When she moved back to Texas I only heard from her once.  But now she's moved back to Dillon, permenantly from what I've heard.  She was 11 when she moved away, and now she's 16.  Unfortunetly she hasn't really changed all that much.  Our conversation lasted for about 10 minutes, and most of it was her making plans with me to do this, do that, can I come to your house, can we hang, out, and on and on and on.  Now, I'm not being mean or anything, but I really don't like to hang out with people.  Call me strange, but I only like to go places with someone every once and awhile.  And dad doesn't like for me to have anyone over to the house all that often.  So now I have to deal with this until I move away from here.  Why do all the clingy people choose me?  Why can't they latch onto someone else?  I'm so tired of being the BFF to every person who comes along.  Mom says everyone wants to impress me because I don't act like I want to impress anyone, and she said besides that everyone likes me and that makes some people feel uncomfortable.  Which I really didn't understand, but oh well.  

Anyway, last night I discovered that if I press the vain in the bottom of my palm under the thumb, I can make the blood stop flowing and watch it start flowing again.  COOL!!!  It's blue too, which is wierd.  Ok, now after this and the vampire thing last night everyone thinks I'm strange.

After watching a little of "Queen of the damned" an hour ago, I then proceded to dress up like a vampire, complete with black hair, white face painter, and dripping blood.  I will not post pictures, because, well, they are a little strange.  See people, this is what happens when you are bored!

Playboy gave the talk today.  Staring at him for 45 minutes is too much for me to bear with.  

JT wasn't at the meeting, but Ariel was.  She wanted me to go to Florence with her, and I said yes, (due to boredom) and she later informed me that she couldn't go because she "forgot" her and her mom and JT and her mom were going to NC to shop for dresses for the wedding.  It's SO nice how they invite me to go places with them.  

Anyway, I showed Playboy my camera and he oohed and awed over it and said he's going to get one.  Maybe I shouldn't have taken it to the meeting.  I don't know, I have this feeling that no one likes me because I have alot of stuff.  We are one of two white families in our congregation, and everyone thinks our two families are rolling in dough and can buy anything we want and go on as many vacations as we want.  We do buy alot of stuff, and go on alot of vacations, but we aren't rich.  We just have the means to buy stuff because my dad is really tight with his money so he has alot of it.  Also, the Granthams are rich because brother Grantham owns his own construction company.  I'm just sick of no one inviting me anywhere, and I think this is the reason why.  

Oh yeah I found a GIF maker!  Yay!  And it's simple!  Woo Raw!
I just took everyone off my friends list who hadn't added me.  So there.  Fool.  Yeah.  Whut.

I got both of the CD's downloaded finally, but the stupid WMP is messed up so I can't burn them.  The MCR CD sounds really good, of what I've listened to.

I went to walmart earlier and got some fishnet stockings and a $30 battery charger, something I couldn't afford but needed.  It charges in only 15 minutes.  I was going to buy that messanger bag I wanted but I didn't have enough to get both.  

I NEED a free GIF editor.  Please, someone, anyone, GIVE ME A LINK!!  I can't find a good GIF creater anywhere.  Well, a good free one anyhow.

I burned the top of my mouth at dinner tonight.  Now it tastes nasty.  But you probably didn't want to know that.  <silence>

No one but Elizabeth comments in here anymore.  :(  

I have been forgotten.  

Goodnight.

Ugh, I feel horrible.  I just woke up after a 2 hour (well, actually a one hour because mom kept talking and banging around in the kitchen) nap.  I still can't find a free GIF maker, and evertime I ask in an icon community everyone ignores me.  I refuse to pay $100 for adobe, if that's how much it costs.  Even if it's less, that's asking a bit too much.  

Anyway, I watched Coheed and Cambria's video for "Blood Red Summer" this afternoon.  Weird, but a good video.  I didn't think it was as good as AFHA, though.

We are having pizza for dinner, yay!  

Oh yeah, JT gave me a shirt last night at the meeting.  They bought it for me but it's WAY too big, (I hope they meant it as a joke, I sure as heck don't wear a 23/24).  I doubt it if they would care if I took it back and exchanged it for something else.  I can get my messanger bag if I do that.  Or maybe it will pay some towards my charger.  Whatever it really helps me out.  They were kind to think of me, and I wish I could wear it because it's cute, but it falls off me.  Literally.  I told mom I was going to wear it anyway to be nice but she said there was no way I was walking out of this house in a shirt that would fit two of me in it and that falls off my shoulders.

In other news...Elizabeth will be here a week from tomorrow!  I can't wait!  I wonder what mom is having for our early lunch?  I don't think dad is going to be here, though.  He might, but he said he has some "judicial matters" to take care of that day.  

More music downloading tonight.  I have to finish the two I started last night because my sodding computer cut my internet connection.

I stayed up untill 2:00 last night talking to Elizabeth (<lj user="glacierflower">).  We signed up for this advise column and put phony questions in it like "y don't muh boi like me".  It was really funny.  I need more good times like this, it keeps me in touch with the real world.

Kim mentioned to me last night that their is going to be some little party in January, some Costume/fashion show/cookout thing.  I bet it's going to be wild, all our parties are.  I specifically remember the last party where me, jennifer, jt, shawn, jabari, and kaleel spent the whole time in the entrance watching the Even Stevens movie on the TV.  Good times.  The outcast convention, we called it.  

Mom is still trying to fix her sodding computer.  I'm really really tired of it.  If she crys one more time I'm going to leave.

I really hate WinMX.  It's so slow and old fashioned looking.  I don't know what everyone raves about it for.  I like Shareaza, I love it in fact.  But everytime I go to download stuff it says that i can't connect.  Now i'm downloading the 2.1 version, hopefully it will work better

I'm going to burn some CD's tonight.  I can't decide which of the five I want to do.  Probably I'll do My Chemical Romance and Jimmy Eat World.  

Mom got me a chocolate bar from a fundraiser thingy yesterday.  I just ate it, it was SO good.  I haven't had a good chocolate bar in a long time.  

I'm a householder tonight with JT.  Not nervous, but I don't know what to wear.  My digital camera will make it's appearance tonight at the hall.  I have to show the playboy up.  Who does he think he is, rolling up with his technical gadgets?  I'll put that fool in his place.  

Did anybody see Greg talking about his "shizzle" on Whose line last night?  Hilarious!  He was playing "a white boy who has decided to turn street."

I was going to delete this journal, but I think I will wait awhile.  I can't really think of a good name.  So if anyone saw the message I previously had written up here, ignore it.  

I am going to make a new one, though, but now I just have to figure out a name to use.

I feel sick.  Nothing new though.  I did just watch a Whose Line I've never watched before.  It had Greg as a white boy trying to be street in Weird Newscasters.  I love Greg.  Really, I do.  He is my homie.

I should write a book for the NaNoWrMo thing like <lj user="glacierflower"> is doing, but I have no motivation.  Her story is really good.  You can read her progress here: <lj user="thelightkeepers">.  

Anyway, I'm about to do one of those LJ trading card thingys.

Oooh, I look ghetto. My digital camera has already killed it's new batteries, so I have to wait untill I get my charger to use it again. I love my wig. I'm going to wear it to the meeting...hehehehee. Well, maybe not. We had an ok morning in service, I didn't get anyone at the door. I'm off to walk around in my wig and stare at things absently.

It's 12:30, do you know where your kid is?  Not my parents, obviously.

If I have to hear the words "Bush", "Kerry", or "election" one more time I may have to kill myself.

I am so edgy.  We went to CVS tonight and raided the clearance holloween crap.  I got a long black wig.  It rocks.  Pictures to be posted tomorrow.  I also got a black light bulb and an eyeshadow from Excerds.  

I just watched Coyote Ugly.  That movie is so cool.  And that guy, what's his name, the one that was in Riding in Cars with Boys, he is SO cute.  I know, I know, I talk about boys all the time.  But hey, there are NO available men around here, so you have to do something.

Field service tomorrow.  Playboy will most likely not be out.  He hasn't been out for about 4 weeks, boo hoo.  It's better this way, the less I see him the less he can make me feel bad.
Why does this picture look really sexy to me? Mmmm, Greg.

Election day, woo hoo.  I could care less.  Unfortunetly I'm going to have to hear about it all day long.  I laughed so hard when I heard about the show The Daily Show is having tonight called "Prelude to the Recount 2004".  That's exactly what's going to happen.  

I'm going to download some CD's tonight.  I'm going to burn:
LostProphets-Start Something
My Chemical Romance-Three Cheers for Sweet Revenge
Sno Patrol-Final Straw
Three Days Grace-S/T

And MAYBE (I might buy it)
Jimmy Eat World-Futures.

I only burn CD's that I don't want to buy because I only like one song off the whole thing.  There is no need for me to spend $15.00 on a CD if I'm only going to listen to one song.  

I can't find a free GIF maker.  If anyone knows of one, tell me ok?

My new website is up and running.  I know it's nothing special, but I like it.  It's simple, it gets the job done.  Check it out if you want to at http://www.madeupreality.tk.  I still have to iron a few kinks out, but if I do say so myself it's pretty good.

There is no food in this house. But in other news, Elizabeth is coming to my house on the 13th! Yay! I haven't seen her in so long! She's going to stop here on her way to Hilton Head. I want to go with them but dad is dragging his heals about how it's to close to the time we go to the cruise, and all this. Plus I'd have to take my schoolwork with me and after what happened at LK's, he's not letting me do that anymore. But anyway at least she gets to stop here for awhile! My room: My white stripes collection:

Mom is mad at me again because I can't fix her sodding computer.  I wish she would just leave it alone or get it fixed.  Anyway, this is her day to deliver and dad's out so I'm here by myself, hoo-raw.  I had to take a test on Macbeth earlier.  It was sort of hard, but not much.  I didn't even read half of the story, hahaha.  

Ooh, I just watched an episode of ER from 1997 that Ewan Mcgregor was in.  Yum.  I loved his look in the 96-97 period.  He had shaggy hair and it made him look alot younger.  His eyes are amazing.
Please tell me I'm not the only one who thinks Jack looks exactly like the lead singer from My Chemical Romance.

Today was ok.  It wasn't nearly as bad as I thought it was going to be.  There were no young people in they congregation we went to.  They were all 12-15 year olds, and none of them had a i'm-higher-than-though look about them.  We ate lunch with a young couple and their three year old daughter and the couple's parents.  The little girl was adorable; by the end of the meal I was her "big sister" and she was pulling me around by the hand trying to hide.  I love kids sometimes.  I love sweet children, anyhow.  Then after lunch we went to the flea market and I got a 136-compacity CD case for the trip.  Very nice.  I had to start using a second CD case this summer because my old one only held 64.  Now all I need accessory-wise for the cruise is that messenger bag I want.  

I really like my new camera.  The only downside to it is that it uses really expensive memory cards.  They cost about twice as much as a regular one.  Oh well, not like I'm going to get a card anyway.

Which Tic-Tac Flavor Are You?
brought to you by Quizilla Darn it, I wanted Orange.

By the way I CANNOT get A Perfect Circle's cover of "Imagine" out of my head.  It just keeps playing over and over again...but it's such a great song.  The guitar and drums really make the piano sound scary.

I watched the Matrix earlier.  Now I feel like putting on a full-body leather suit and a trench coat and shooting things.  Thankee.

Well, I got a digital camera.  It's the Olympus I was origionally going to get.  I broke down.  I know, I know, I REALLY wanted the Nikon, but I just don't trust those online companies.  There is one perk to me getting the Olympus; it has almost a two inch screen, it's really big.  It's much bigger than all the rest of the digital camera's at the store.  I would post a picture but I'm to tired.  

First we went to the tire place and then walked over to Rosses.  Nobody bought anything, but JT and her mom and Ariel and her mom were there.  More on that later.  Then we went and got the car and then went to kmart.  I got some shampoo and an eyeshadow.  Then on to Zaxby's for dinner.  Then we went to Target and then Sams, and then we came home.  

About the JT and Ariel thing.  It really hurt my feelings.  This is the what, third or fourth time this has happened this month alone?  I'm so tired of it I could scream.  I know I'm not supposed to go anywhere with her, but still.  They could at least invite me.  I'm just plain sick of it.  She knows how it feels to be left out, and yet she does it to me.  Oh well, I'm not going to worry about it because I know she will probably not be in the congregation much longer.  That's a sad thing to say, but it's true.  She has no spiritual inclination whatsoever.  

Oh yeah, Dionisis just made an escape attempt that almost killed him.  He climed on top of his can, grabbed hold of the wire cage top thing we have set up, and pushed himself off of the top of the aquarium onto the floor where he landed on his back.  I grabbed him up and put him back in the cage and he started moving his mouth around funny and grabbing at it.  I thought he was going to die, but he seems ok now. I hope so anyway.  We'll see how he is tomorrow.  

We are off to give the talk tomorrow in Florence.  I'm really nervous.  Extrememly nervous.  I don't know what shoes to wear either.  But maybe I will meet Ryan there, who knows.  You do know who Ryan is, don't you?  Oh well.  Later.

We had an OK morning in service.  The first door we went to we were invited in by a housekeeper and taken into the back room where the people who owned the house was, and when the owner found out who we were he started yelling at us to get out because he was a baptist and he had been through this before and he didn't want to talk to us, etc, etc.  It kind of made me feel bad, but I got over it.  People are so stupid.  It makes me sick.

Anyway, we are off to Florence at 3:00.  We will avoid the pesky tricker treaters at all costs.  I wish the Granthams could come with us but I doubt they can go.  Oh well.

What Unique Award Would YOU Win? (long answers)
brought to you by Quizilla Ah that rocked Ozzy! I especially enjoyed the teenage girl one. ::giggle::

I still have six Gmail invites, if anyone wants them.  I have no use for them, like I said, and I think the link runs out eventually doesn't it?  

Anyway.  My new perfume came.  It's called "Mandarin".  It smells really nice.  Oranges are my favorite smell next to the smell of Disney World.  

We are going to Florence tomorrow to get away from the pesky tricker treaters.

I had to delete my website and start over again.  Well, i didn't have to, as I found out right after I did it.  It turns out my web uploader didn't have their extensions turned on at this time, so I have to do the whole thing over again for nothing.  

I am liking two bands I never thought I would like: The Used and Jimmy Eat World.  I love both of their new songs.  

Updated List of CD's to get:
All Weezer CD's
The Deftones- White Pony and S/T
The Used-In Love and Death
Jimmy Eat World-Futures
All Incubus CD's except A Crow left of the murder
The Yeah Yeah Yeah's Machine EP

When I am bored, I make lists:

STUFF I NEED FOR CRUISE:

A couple pairs of pants, maybe Hot Topic bondage or some new cords.
A few shirts, QUALITY MADE shirts, not cheap crap that shrinks.
That messanger bag I wanted
GET DAD TO ORDER DIGITAL CAMERA!  (He's dragging his feet, it's really annoying.)
Burn some new CD's (i'm saving money for the cruise)

I really hate Microsoft Frontpage.  It's so confusing and I can't get my website to upload right.

It's raining and cold here.  Nothing new.  I couldn't see the eclipse last night because of the stupid clouds.  I really wanted to see it.  :(

I'm still having trouble uploading my website.  When I go to publish my web, the address won't change from my last web provider.  

Oh yeah, I have six G-Mail invites.  If anyone wants one, comment and give me your email address and I will send you one.  I have no use for them, so if you need one, just say so.

I've got my new website done.  All I have to do now is upload it.  I signed up for a really good service today but I can't seem to login to their site, so I'm going to do it tomorrow.  It's really nice, I like it.  It's simple, but it's well designed.

I had a good day in service.  I worked with Shayna.  She's cool, we need to do more stuff together.  We talked about her and Jennifer and about the problems in the other congregations.  Then after service we went to Mcdonalds for lunch and I got one of thier Philly Cheese steak subs.  It was ok, but it was nothing like Brother Lances' sandwiches.  I really miss those.  I haven't had one of those in a long time.  

Sorry Ozzy, we can't go with you to Hilton Head.  My dad said we can't go because it's too far away and we are leaving to go on the cruise a few days after that.  Speaking of the cruise, new clothes, a new bag, some new shoes, and other crap is needed for the trip.  I must go shopping.

Amazingly I'm not even tired from my late-night computering.  Mom didn't wake me up until like 30 minutes after nine, so we got into a fight over that.  

I just found out that we have to go to Florence Sunday because dad is giving the talk.  Given what happened last time, I'm thinking of staying here.  No more snotty let's-pump-information-out-of-her girls for me.  

I have resigned to my fate about the cruise.  Five years.  I should have known.

I made my dream journal thingy.  I'm not going to post it, though.  Or maybe I will.  I don't know.

Women always put men first.  That's all I'm going to say.

I just cleaned Dionisis's cage.  He's been peeing in his sleep can and sleeping in a mound of bedding on one side of the cage.  I think the peeing-in-a-can thing is really nice.  At least his whole cage doesn't smell horrible.  

We are going to Walmart tonight, woot!  Yeah!  Party!  Yee-haw!  Woopeee!  Ok, I digress.  

Before I cleaned the hamsters cage I layed in bed for 2 1/2 hours and tried to sleep.  I didn't succeed.

I had a bible study today with one of my calls.  It's a little weird listening to myself talk, if you know what I mean.  I can't get my words out right sometimes, and it makes me mad because I know what I want to say but I can't put it in words.  I know what I mean, but it's like I can't say it because it comes out wrong.  I'm such a spaz.  

I need new clothes for the cruise.  

Oh yeah, I looked up some of these LJ witness sites on here, and I'm sorry to say most of them don't sound too wittnessy.  That's really sad.  I wouldn't post in any of them.  They sound a little bit fake to me.  Do you post in them Ozzy?

It's so boring on here at night.  No one is ever on.  Arthur is on, but he is ignoring me now so forget that.  Childish.  So childish.  

I might as well go to bed, there is nothing to do anyway.

I'm on at night again...super-slueth that I am.  I can't sleep.  I don't know why.  

Now I can't think of anything to say.  I think I will go make some Whose line avatars.

We got back from Florence around 7:00. It was ok, nothing special. I didn't buy anything. We weren't at the mall for very long, maybe 20 minutes or so. I saw a beautiful shirt I wanted at the Hot Topic, but I resisted because I've finally agreed on the digital camera I wanted and I don't want daddy saying I ask for too much. Here's the one: And I AM NOT changing my mind this time. This is definetly the one. It's only $167.00 because nikon is offering a $100.00 mail in rebate. The Olympus one I wanted doesn't come with a charger like the nikon does, and the olympus uses a special kind of card that is very expensive. Anyway. We ate at taco bell. I got a chalupa. Yum yum. The bread on that thing is great. Ok, no one cares.

Wow.  I just downloaded and listened to the Boll Weevil song where Jack cusses out the moshers.  FUNNY!!!!!  I would have loved to have been there.  Seriously, how can you mosh to Boll Weevil??  Come on.  I've never heard him that angry before.  But that was so funny.  

Well, that was the highlight of my day.  Oh wait I'm going to Hot Topic tonight!!  Yay!!  More bondage pants please!

I had to do another scavenger hunt this afternoon for my stupid Gym.  

I don't feel like talking about it.  

I'm 17 years old, I go to homeschool, I have very few if no friends, I have no car, I have no boyfriend.

Boring night last night.  It's really dark here, I think it's going to rain.  Dad is outside messing about with his chainsaw, I'm trying to avoid having to take him to the hospital to get his hand sewn back on.  

Oh yeah, did I mention that LK IS going with us to Disney World even though she said she wasn't?  She is going to ruin everything.  She's already bought her tickets AND booked at a hotel room that we aren't going to stay at, and she expects us to stay there too.  I'm so tired of her making everyone's plans for them.  I want to stay at the place we stayed last year.  

BLAH BLAH BLAH BLAH.

I had to work with Denzel this morning.  I had to constantly keep his hands off me and keep him from looking down my shirt the whole morning.  Why do I even bother?  And now Sister Wallace is talking about coming with us on the cruise!  No!!!!  Denzel will go if they go.  I would hang myself on the spot if she told me they were going with us.  Elizabeth and her family might go.  Mrs. Elizabeth's mother, if you are reading this, PLEASE GO WITH US ON OUR CRUISE!!!  I BEG YOU!!  SAVE ME FROM THE CLUTCHES OF A 12 YEAR OLD SUITOR!!!  

Ok I will calm down now.  I really hope they can go, though.  I miss Ozzy, I haven't seen her for a year and a half.  And, think of the fun time we would have!!  

I have to go back to school now.  Ho-Hum.
